# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cross-Modal Cartographer — environment template
#
# NONE of these are required to run the web app. The backend loads its FAISS
# index from backend/artifacts/ and builds the Knowledge Graph in-memory from
# the index metadata, so it runs on a fresh clone with zero configuration.
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in only the values you need:
#     cp .env.example .env
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# (Optional) Render result THUMBNAILS by pointing at a local copy of the images.
# Search, similarity scores and KG facts all work without these.
#   IMAGES_DIR         → a folder containing an images/ subdirectory (main dataset)
#   ANDITO_IMAGES_DIR  → a flat folder of GLD (Google Landmarks) images
# IMAGES_DIR=/absolute/path/to/dataset
# ANDITO_IMAGES_DIR=/absolute/path/to/gld/images

# (Optional) Cloud Neo4j AuraDB — only for rebuilding the graph via the pipeline
# scripts (populate_neo4j.py). The running app does NOT use these.
# Create a free instance at https://console.neo4j.io
# NEO4J_URI=neo4j+s://<your-instance-id>.databases.neo4j.io
# NEO4J_USER=neo4j
# NEO4J_PASSWORD=<your-password>

# (Optional) Hugging Face token — only for downloading the GLD dataset subset.
# HF_TOKEN=hf_<your-token>
